The number of coronavirus cases in South Africa has increased to 1 532 497 after the country identified 1 531 new cases since the last report. In a statement, the Department of Health has also reported a further 74 COVID-19 related deaths. “Eastern Cape 1, Free State 15, Gauteng 38, Kwa-Zulu Natal 4, Limpopo 1, Mpumalanga 7, North West 0, Northern Cape 2 and Western Cape 6.” This brings the total to 51 634 deaths. Recoveries now stand at 1 459 056, representing a recovery rate of 95%. The number of healthcare workers vaccinated under the Sisonke Programme is 168 413. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 17 March. Use the COVID Alert SA app to protect yourself, your loved ones and your community. Start using this privacy preserving app today. Add your phone to the fight! Download the Covid Alert SA app now! https://t.co/8YKEqaiiRF pic.twitter.com/VFZoNPeiVe — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) March 17, 2021 